verbose_text: Moreover, the internal fragment at m/z 530.2 and a further fragment at m/z 529.2 support the presence of a Hep unit substituted by two HexN residues, of which one is methylated, as outlined in Figure XREF_FIG a. Indeed, the occurrence of minor OS peaks at m/z 1455.6 and 911.5 (Deltam/z 14) implied that the methylation on the HexN residue was nonstoichiometric.
